The power utility says it needs between 4,000 and 6,000 megawatts of extra generation capacity to keep the lights on while it maintains old generators. eNCA's Govan Whittles reports. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Eskom has recorded its highest number of trips at power stations on record at 697, nearly double it expected this year. The power utility says it needs between 4,000 and 6,000 megawatts of extra generation capacity to keep the lights on while it maintains old generators. READ:Â De Ruyter: Eskom working to bring additional capacity online Eskom also announced not a single power station in the country is running at full capacity and is calling on the private sector to help. It warns that it will need to burn billions of rand in diesel to keep the lights on this winter and this makes rolling power cuts highly likely. * eNCA's Govan Whittles reports.